        "subject": "LU-13643 llite: add mirror detection for concurrent write",
        "message": "LU-13643 llite: add mirror detection for concurrent write\n\nThis patch implements the foundation for concurrent write\nfunctionality on immediate mirrored files by adding mirror\ndetection capabilities to the client.\n\nKey changes:\n- Add ll_get_mirror_info() function to detect mirrored files\n  with immediate flag using cl_object_layout_get()\n- Integrate mirror detection into ll_file_io_generic() for\n  write operations\n- Add server-side FLR state transition support in mdt_open.c\n  for ACTIVE_WRITER intent handling\n- Files correctly transition to WRITE_PENDING state on write\n  operations to immediate mirrored files\n\nThe implementation uses a safe approach with proper buffer\nallocation and error handling to avoid kernel crashes.\nServer-side integration ensures FLR state transitions work\ncorrectly with the existing mirroring infrastructure.\n\nThis establishes the foundation for concurrent write locks\nthat will allow multiple writers to immediate mirrored files\nwhile maintaining data consistency through automatic mirror\nstaling mechanisms.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5073bc918034b1f9434b7edd49bb14d73df3aa25\n"
